org.eng.aisp

Interface IDataWindow<DATA>

  • Type Parameters:
    DATA -
    All Superinterfaces:
    IInstanceID, Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDoubleFeature, IDoubleWindow, IFeature<FDATA>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractDataWindow, DoubleFeature, DoubleWindow, SoundClip, SoundRecordingMetaData.SoundClipMetaData

    public interface IDataWindow<DATA>
extends IInstanceID, Serializable
    Defines the base functionality for a window of generic data. Data windows have a begin and start time. The interface anticipates multi-variate data through 0-based indexing to get the data, sampling sizes and sampling rates.
    Author:
    dawood

        double getStartTimeMsec()
        Get the time corresponding to the beginning of the data window. Units are undefined, but strongly recommended to be milliseconds since the epoch.
        Returns:
        number of milliseconds since the time 00:00:00 UTC on January 1, 1970.

      • getEndTimeMsec

        double getEndTimeMsec()
        Get the time corresponding to the endo of the data window. Units are undefined, but strongly recommended to be milliseconds since the epoch.
        Returns:
        number of milliseconds since the time 00:00:00 UTC on January 1, 1970.

        Get the length of the clip in milliseconds.

      • splitOnTime

        List<? extends IDataWindow<DATA>> splitOnTime(double durationMsec,
                                              boolean keepPartialWindow)
        Split this window into 1 or more consecutive sub-windows of the given length specified in time. All context is copied to the new windows. Start and stop times are adjusted accordingly in the new windows.
        Parameters:
        durationMsec - length of each window in milliseconds.
        keepPartialWindow - if true, then the last window may be made of up less than the requested number of samples. If false, then a partial last window is not included in the returned list.
        Returns:
        a list of consecutive windows that, if possible, overlap at their start and end and the are as close to the given duration as possible given the window's sampling rate.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if samplesPerWindow 0 or less, or iis larger than this window.

      • subWindow

        IDataWindow<DATA> subWindow(double startMsec,
                            double endMsec)
        Get a subwindow with the given start and end time. If either time does not fall exactly on a sample time, then only samples inside, inclusive, of the given times are included in the returned window.
        Parameters:
        startMsec - start time in milliseconds of resulting window in the same units returned by getStartTimeMsec(), inclusive.
        endMsec - end time in milliseconds of resulting window in the same units returned by getStartTimeMsec(), inclusive.
        Returns:
        null if either startMsec or endMsec are outside the window.

      • subWindow2

        IDataWindow<DATA> subWindow2(double startOffsetMsec,
                             double endOffsetMsec)
        Get a subwindow with the given offsets into this window (an alternative to subWindow(double, double)). If either time does not fall exactly on a sample time, then only samples inside, inclusive, of the given times are included in the returned window.
        Parameters:
        startMsec - 0-based time offset in milliseconds into this window from which to start the returned window, inclusive. Must be 0 or larger and less than the duration of this window.
        endMsec - 0-based time offset in milliseconds into this window that defines the end of the returned window, inclusive. Must be 0 or larger and less than the duration of this window.
        endMsec - end time of resulting window in the same units returned by getStartTimeMsec(), inclusive.
        Returns:
        null if either startMsec or endMsec are outside the window.

      • resize

        IDataWindow<DATA> resize(double durationMsec,
                         IDataWindow.PadType padType)
        Create a new window based on this instance that is of the given duration. If the current window is larger than the requested size, then a sub clip starting at the front is generated. If the current window is smaller than the requested size, then then padding is added to create a new window of the requested length.
        Parameters:
        durationMsec - length of time in milliseconds the returned window is to cover.
        padType - one of IDataWindow.PadType.ZeroPad or IDataWindow.PadType.DuplicatePad controlling what data is used to pad the data.
        Returns:
        a new window with the same start time, and sampling rate as this instance and with the requested duration.

      • getIndependentValues

        double[] getIndependentValues()
        Get the independent values on which the dependent data values in this window dependent. In many cases this may be time and derived from the start time, end time and sampling rate. However, some implementations (e.g. features such as FFT and DCT) may define their own.
        Returns:

        Get the rate (samples/second) at which the data in this window was sampled.
        Returns:
